title.narrative: 3.3. EQUITABLE ACCESS TO YOUTH SERVICES

description.narrative: Adolescents have equitable access to comprehensive services provided by Youth Houses, functioning in compliance with national standards, which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Empowerment (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The most deprived adolescents empowered and resilient to become social change agents towards creating more tolerant, peaceful and inclusive societies
